properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 4:27AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THIS MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY WITH
ACCUMULATING SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW ALONG THE SOUTH SHORE...

.Snow and lake effect snow will impact the South Shore Wednesday
through Thursday morning. The greatest snowfall accumulations of
4 to 8 inches are forecast for the northern portions of Ashland
and Iron counties, with lesser amounts of 2 to 5 inches
elsewhere. Blowing snow and dangerous wind chills to 35 below are
also expected.

Bitterly cold wind chills are expected across northeastern
Minnesota and northwestern Wisconsin late this morning through
Thursday. Wind chill values as low as -30 will be possible across
northeastern Minnesota late this morning through the afternoon.
Tonight into Thursday morning, widespread wind chill values
ranging from -20 to -40 are likely away from Lake Superior with
some values approaching -50 near the International Border.

* WHAT...Snow and lake effect snow expected. Total snow
accumulations of 2 to 5 inches, with higher amounts of 4 to 8
inches for northern Iron and Ashland counties.

* WHERE...Douglas, Bayfield, Ashland and Iron Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Red Cliff Band and the Bad
River Reservation.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Wednesday to noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. Blowing
snow will further reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road
conditions can also be found at 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST THURSDAY
